language.title: Bot Language
language.description: The current bots language is set to **{{ .language_current }}**.

language_reset.description:
You have reset this servers Levely bot language to default(English)!

If you would like to change this type `/opt {{ .opt_old_status }}` to change your status!

opt_change.title: Opt Status

upvote.title: Upvote
upvote.description:
Upvote Levely to learn exclusive perks only granted when upvoting.
[Upvote here]({{ .upvote_url }})

To claim your perks, check out the `/credit` command!

difficulty.title: Difficulty
difficulty.description:
**Current Set Difficulty**: {{ .server_difficulty_level }}

To change the current set difficulty use `/difficulty {{ .server_difficulty_options }}`

difficulty_max.title: Difficulty Invalid
difficulty_max.description:
Difficulty `{{ .difficulty_invalid }}` is an invalid option please choose `{{ .server_difficulty_options }}` difficulty.

Using `/difficulty {{ .server_difficulty_options }}` will change the servers current set difficulty.

difficulty_duplicate.title: Difficulty
difficulty_duplicate.description:
This servers difficulty is already set to difficulty `{{ .difficulty_duplicate }}`.

If you would like to change use that use `/difficulty {{ .server_difficulty_options }}`

difficulty_updated.title: Difficulty Updated
difficulty_updated.description:
**New Difficulty**: `{{ .server_difficulty_level }}`
**Old Difficulty**: `{{ .difficulty_before }}`

Using `/difficulty {{ .server_difficulty_options }}` will change the servers current set difficulty.

premium_required.title: Premium Required
premium_required.description:
[Premium is required, purchase premium to access this command.]({{ .premium_url }})

rewards_nicknameformat_not_specified.title: Nickname format not specified
rewards_nicknameformat_not_specified.description: You have not specified a Nickname format.

rewards_leaderboard_rank_not_specified.title: Rank not specified
rewards_leaderboard_rank_not_specified.description: You have not specified a leaderboard rank position.

rewards_emoji_set.title: Emoji Restrictions Updated

rewards_emoji_clear.title: Emoji(s) Restrictions Cleared
rewards_emoji_clear.description:
You have cleared all set restrictions for {{ .rewards_emoji_role_cleared }}.

Setup new restrictions with `/rewards emoji set [@RoleExample] [:Emoji:]`.
Do not include [] in the command executed.

rewards_emoji_remove.title: Emoji(s) Restriction Removed
rewards_emoji_remove.description:
**Emoji**: {{ .rewards_emoji_removed }} **removed from** {{ .rewards_emoji_role_removed }}.

Setup new restrictions with `/rewards emoji set [@RoleExample] [:Emoji:]`.
Do not include [] in the command executed.

rewards_emoji_not_specified.title: Emoji not specified
rewards_emoji_not_specified.description: You have not specified a restricted emoji please select a minimum 1.

rewards_role_set.title: Role Set
rewards_role_set.description:
**Role**: {{ .rewards_role_set }} **set to** {{ .rewards_role_level_set }}.

Add additional role rewards with `/rewards role set [PUT-LEVEL] [@RoleExample]`.
Do not include [] in the command executed.

rewards_role_clear.title: Role Cleared

rewards_role_not_specified.title: Role not specified
rewards_role_not_specified.description:
The role reward has not been set due to not being specified.

Command Example: `/rewards role set` [PUT-LEVEL] [@RoleExample]`.
Do not include [] in the command executed.

rewards_role_doesnt_exist.title: Role doesn't exist
rewards_role_doesnt_exist.description:
The role/level reward does not seem to excist please try again.
[If this is an issue that can not be resolved contact support.]{{ .support_url }}

Command Example: `/rewards role set` [PUT-LEVEL] [@RoleExample]`.
Do not include [] in the command executed.

rewards_role_override.title: Role alread in use
rewards_role_override.descriptions:
{{ .reward_role_override }} has been already set to level {{ .rewards_role_level_override }}.
You may override this by clicking the confirm button below else click cancel.
Please choose another role or clear the set reward.

rewards_role_override_confirmed.title: Role override confirmed
rewards_role_override_confirmed.description: You have confirmed {{ .reward_role_override }} override being set to level **{{ .rewards_role_level_override }**.

rewards_role_canceled.title: Role override canceled
rewards_role_canceled.description: You have canceled {{ .reward_role_override }} override being set to level **{{ .rewards_role_level_override }**.

manage_reset.title: Manage Reset {{ .manage_reset_type }}
manage_reset.description: {{ .manage_reset_target }} progression has been reset to default!

manage_reset_confirm.title: Manage Reset Confirmation
manage_reset_confirm.description: Please confirm your reset confirmation for {{ .manage_reset_type }}.

setup_reward_roles.title: Welcome to Levely!
setup_reward_roles.description: Would you like for Levely to generate role rewards for you? If so, you'll notice 3 new roles in your server: Level 5, Level 10 and Level 20. If you'd rather set this up yourself, you can skip this step.

setup_difficulty_selection.title: Welcome to Levely!
setup_difficulty_selection.description: Set a difficulty level for experience (EXP for short) gained by your community members. Lower the number, the easier it is to level-up and the higher the number, the harder it would be to level up. This can be changed any time with /settings difficulty.

setup_announcement_selection.title: Welcome to Levely!
setup_announcement_selection.description: Setup a dedicated channel for level-up messages and reward roles being given out by providing a channel ID or mentioning the channel. Otherwise the messages will be sent to the latest channel the user leveled up in and will automatically delete within 30 seconds after. If you would like to disable this please select the disable button below, otherwise click the Provide Channel button for further instructions.

setup_logging_selection.title: Welcome to Levely!
setup_logging_selection.description: Audit logs are provided for things not shown set it up by providing a channel ID or mentioning a channel. If you would like to disable this please select the disable button below, otherwise click the Provide Channel button for further instructions.

setup_complete.title: Welcome to Levely!
setup_complete.description:
Levely has been successfully set up! You won't regret adding Levely. ðŸ˜Ž

:information_source: Did you know we can import from Mee6 and Arcane? Try it out by clicking any of the 3 buttons below and let Levely take over from there. *If you'd rather start fresh, then you don't need to click anything.*

difficulty_information.title: Difficulty Information
difficulty_information.description: The difficulty is used to determine the amount of XP you'll need to level up. Would you like to `Change` the current difficulty for the server or `Reset` it back to default (3)?

info.title: Server Logging
info.description: Levely has the ability to log anything internal related, from commands executed to users changed and rewards given out. What would you like to do with this module?

base.title: Admin Information
base.description:
Levely Admins refer to certain roles in your server that "act" as if they have administrator permissions but don't. This is a safer approach if you'd like to trust a certain handful of members with changing important settings or modifying users within Levely.
Would you like to `Add` a role to the administrator list or `remove` one from it?

add.title: Admin Information
add.description: Please respond by mentioning the role (not advised) or providing a Role ID. If you don't know how to get the ID and would like to avoid pure chaos from ensuing over a mention, [read this helpful guide](https://support.discord.com/hc/en-us/articles/206346498-Where-can-I-find-my-User-Server-Message-ID-) provided by Discord.

remove.title: Admin Information
remove.description: Select a role you'd like to no longer have as a Levely Administrator.

post_save.title: Admin Information
post_save.description: {{ .role }} has been {{ .action }} the list of Administrators for managing Levely settings in this server.

error.title: Admin Information
error.description:
Something went wrong when adding the role as a Levely Administrator.
{{ .error }}

prompt.title: Server Announcements
prompt.description: Levely can send messages to a dedicated channel with level up messages, reward messages, or if you'd prefer.. you can split it up between different channels! Would you like to configure `Level Up` messages or `Reward` messages? You can also configure `Both` at the same time.

where_send.title: Server Announcements
where_send.description:
Would you still like for Levely to send to a dedicated channel, or reply to the message that caused the user to Level Up/earn a reward?
If you'd prefer, you can click `Toggle Mentions` now to enable/disable the mention for either option.

channel_prompt.title: Server Announcements
channel_prompt.description: Please mention the channel or provide an ID for the channel where Levely will send the announcements.

post_save.title: Server Announcements
post_save.description: Success! Your new configuration has been saved and is already in effect. Announcements will now be sent to {{ .new_data }}.

error.title: Server Announcements
error.description:
Something went wrong when configuring the announcements.
{{ .error }}

set.title: Server Difficulty
set.description: Select a difficulty beteween 1-5 (1-10 if you're a premium server), 1 being the easiest, 5 being the hardest for free servers, medium for premium servers and 10 being the hardest.

save.title: Server Difficulty
save.description: Success! The difficulty for the server has been set as {{ .new }} and is already in effect.

info.title: Server Logging
info.description: Levely has the ability to log anything internal related, from commands executed to users changed and rewards given out. What would you like to do with this module?

cprompt.title: Server Logging
cprompt.description:
Please provide a channel for this server that Levely has access to send messages and embed links in. Without those two permissions, logs may fail to send.
You can provide a direct mention to the channel or a channel ID.

save.title: Server Logging
save.description: Success! The logging for the server has been saved and is now in effect.

toggle.title: Server Logging
toggle.description: Using the buttons below, click one of them to set your logging preferences. Once done, you may click **Save** to continue.

info.title: Server Multipliers
info.description: Levely gives you the ability to multiply the amount of XP given out with certain roles. Useful for rewarding donators and server boosters. What would you like to do with this module?

add.title: Server Multipliers
add.description:
Please provide a role that Levely should bind the multiplier out to.
You can provide a direct mention to the role or a role ID.

set.title: Server Multipliers
set.description:
Please provide a multiplier for the role you provided.
The multiplier should be a number between 1 and 10, 1 being the lowest and 10 being the highest. If you'd like a mulitplier over 3, you must be in a premium server.

remove.title: Server Multipliers
remove.description:
Please provide a role that Levely should remove the multiplier from.
You can provide a direct mention to the role or a role ID.

save.title: Server Multipliers
save.description: Success! The multipliers for the server have been saved and are now in effect.

info.title: Server Restrictions
info.description: Levely gives you the ability to restrict certain roles from using certain commands or from earning experience in certain channels. What would you like to do with this module?

type.title: Server Restrictions
type.description:
Please provide the type of restriction.
- Channel: Applies to that channel as a whole.
- Role: Applies to that role as a whole. (Global)

channel.title: Server Restrictions
channel.description:
Please provide the channel that you'd like to restrict.
You can provide a direct mention to the channel or a channel ID.

role.title: Server Restrictions
role.description:
Please provide the role that you'd like to restrict.
You can provide a direct mention to the role or a role ID.

channel-r.title: Server Restrictions
channel-r.description:
Please provide the channel that you'd like to unrestrict.
You can provide a direct mention to the channel or a channel ID.

role-r.title: Server Restrictions
role-r.description:
Please provide the role that you'd like to unrestrict.
You can provide a direct mention to the role or a role ID.

type2.title: Server Restrictions
type2.description:
Please provide the type of restriction.
- Experience Gained: Prevents the user within that channel/role from earning exp.
- Commands: Applies to any command that Levely has.

save.title: Server Restrictions
save.description: Success! The restrictions for the server have been saved and are now in effect.

base.title: Prestige Information
base.description:
Prestiges are a way to enhance your server's rewards and rewarding those who have good activity.
 Either way, what would you like to do?

add.title: Prestige Information
add.description: Please provide the role you'd like to be handed out as a prestige. You can provide a direct mention to the role or a role ID.

level.title: Prestige Information
level.description: Please provide the level that the user should have to earn the prestige.

post_save.title: Prestige Information
post_save.description: Success! {{ .role }} has been {{ .action }} the current list of prestiges offered.

error.title: Prestige Information
error.description:
An error occurred while trying to save the prestige information.
{{ .error }}

remove.title: Prestige Information
remove.description: Please provide the role you'd like to be removed from the prestige list. You can provide a direct mention to the role or a role ID.

base.title: Settings Overview
base.description: You can configure the settings below by using their respective `/` commands listed beside the title of each field.

base.title: Error
base.description:
An error occurred while trying to process your request.
```{{ .error }}```

base.title: Help Menu
base.description:
[Website]({{ .website_url }}) | [Invite Bot]({{ .invite_url }}) | [Support Server]({{ .support_url }}) | [Dashboard]({{ .dashboard_url }})

` Description `
Levely is an all-in-one discord leaderboard and analytics bot with integration amongst various platforms. With a comprehensive leveling system, your server now has the ability to rewards players for levels.

` Navigation `
Below is a little selection prompt. Click/Tap on it to see the different categories Levely has to offer.

base.title: Thanks for inviting Levely!
base.description:
[Website]({{ .website_url }}) | [Invite Bot]({{ .invite_url }}) | [Support Server]({{ .support_url }}) | [Dashboard]({{ .dashboard_url }})

Levely is an all-in-one discord leaderboard and analytics bot with integration amongst various platforms. With a comprehensive leveling system, your server now has the ability to rewards players for levels.

To make your setup process easier, just click the button below to get started. Or don't, we really can't tell you what to do. ðŸ˜‰

invalid.title: Code Redemption Failure
invalid.description: The code provided (`{{ .redeem_code }}`) is invalid. Please make sure the code you provided is correctly copied/pasted/typed. If you think your code should've worked, contact [Levely Support]({{ .support_url }}).

prompt.title: Prestige / Level Rewards
prompt.description: Levely can provide roles for different levels. Would you like to add a reward or remove one?

add.title: Prestige / Level Rewards
add.description: Please provide the Role ID or mention the role that you'd like to add as a reward.

add2.title: Prestige / Level Rewards
add2.description: Please provide the level this role should be granted to the user.

remove.title: Prestige / Level Rewards
remove.description: Please provide the Role ID or mention the role that you'd like to remove as a reward.

prompt.title: Leaderboard Rewards
prompt.description:
Wanna make the leaderboard more fun ~~and more competitive~~? Let Levely give you a reward for each podium position. #1 has never felt more golden.
Would you like to add a podium reward or remove one?

add.title: Leaderboard Rewards
add.description: Click on any of the podium places below you'd like to set a reward for..

add2.title: Leaderboard Rewards
add2.description: Please provide the role that should be handed out. You can mention the role or provide the ID for said role.

prompt.title: Emoji Rewards
prompt.description: Levely can lock/restrict emojis to different levels. Would you like to add a restricted emoji or remove one?

add.title: Emoji Rewards
add.description: Please provide the emoji that you'd like to add as a reward.

add2.title: Emoji Rewards
add2.description: Please provide the role that this emoji should be locked to. Locking an emoji prevents anyone who doesn't have the role from using it.

remove.title: Emoji Rewards
remove.description: Please provide the emoji that you'd like to remove as a reward.

remove2.title: Emoji Rewards
remove2.description: Please select the role that this emoji should be unlocked from. You may select multiple roles from the dropdown below.

prompt.title: Automatic Role Assignment
prompt.description: Levely can also add roles to user on join. Just to keep it simplified to one bot, would you like to add roles to the welcome list or remove them?

add.title: Automatic Role Assignment
add.description: Provide a space separated list of roles that you'd like to add to the welcome list. You can mention those roles or provide the IDs for said roles. *See example below.*

remove.title: Automatic Role Assignment
remove.description: Provide a space separated list of roles that you'd like to remove from the welcome list. You can mention those roles or provide the IDs for said roles. *See example below.*

confsave.title: Configuration Saved
confsave.description: Your configuration has been saved. It should now be in effect. If it doesn't seem to be in effect, wait 5-10 minutes then contact [Levely Support]({{ .support_url }}).

resetconfirm.title: Wait!
resetconfirm.description: Are you sure that you'd like to reset this option? This action cannot be undone.

coupon_gen.title: Coupon Generated
coupon_gen.description:
A coupon for {{ .service }} has been generated.

Your code is:
```
{{ .code }}```
This code expires in {{ .exp }}.

coupon_gen_pub.title: Coupon Generation
coupon_gen_pub.description: A coupon has been generated! Check your DMs.

coupon_gen_pub2.title: Coupon Generation
coupon_gen_pub2.description: A coupon has been generated and sent out to the user.

cr_error.title: Coupon Revocation
cr_error.description: Levely had a bit of trouble finding the coupon to revoke. Please try the command again.

cr_success.title: Coupon Revocation
cr_success.description: Levely has successfully revoked the coupon provided.

info.title: Levely + Reaction Roles
info.description: Levely makes is easy to setup & maintain reaction roles for your server. Select an option below to continue.

add1.title: Reaction Roles Setup
add1.description:
Please provide a role that Levely should bind the reaction to.
You can provide a direct mention to the role or a role ID.

add2.title: Reaction Roles Setup
add2.description:
Please provide the text that Levely should display for the role.
For example, if the role you'd like to add is `Giveaways Ping`, you would enter `Giveaways` if the panel is for announcements/notifications.

add3.title: Reaction Roles Setup
add3.description: If you already have a panel setup with Levely, please provide the message ID for it now. If not, just respond with `Create Panel` and Levely will make one for you.

add4.title: Reaction Roles Setup
add4.description: Where would you like to send the panel to? You can send it to any channel as long as users have the ability to **view** the channel.

add5.title: Reaction Roles Setup
add5.description: The panel has successfully been found. What would you like to name the embed? This could be `Notification Roles`, `Preferred Pings`, etc.

remove1.title: Reaction Roles Setup
remove1.description: Please provide the channel that contains the reaction roles you'd like to modify. You may mention the channel or provide a channel ID.

remove2.title: Reaction Roles Setup
remove2.description: Please provide the message ID for the reaction roles you'd like to modify. If you don't know the message ID, you can find it by looking for any message by Levely in the channel you provided.

remove3.title: Reaction Roles Setup
remove3.description: Please select the role that you'd like to remove from the menu below.

error.title: Reaction Roles Setup
error.description: Levely had a bit of trouble finding something with the information you provided. Please try the command again.

complete.title: Reaction Roles Setup
complete.description: You're all set. The panel has been updated with your selections.

complete.title: Import from Another Service
complete.description: Levely has successfully imported data and is now up to date. Have fun!

not_enough_users.title: Leaderboard
not_enough_users.description: Unable to show the leaderboard as there was not enough users to generate a leaderboard.

overview.title: Levely Rewards
overview.description:
Levely has a built-in credit system that rewards users for voting and giving exposure to Levely.

You currently have **{{ .credits }}** credits.
You last voted on **{{ .last_vote_time }}** and can vote again **{{ .next_vote_time }}** through **{{ .platform }}**.
{{ .active }}

To trade in your credits for rewards, use the `/creditredeem` command.

redeem.title: Levely Rewards
redeem.description:
Welcome to our rewards area! We currently offer premium features for users who have voted for Levely. You may click a button below to redeem your credits for a premium feature.

The cost of premium is as listed below:
The buttons are represented as days. 2 days, 4 days, 8 days and 12 days.
2 days = 4 credits, 4 days = 8 credits, 8 days = 16 credits, 12 days = 24 credits.

redeem_error.title: Levely Rewards
redeem_error.description: There was a bit of trouble trying to exchange your credits for a subscription. This may be due to you not having enough credits or the subscription you're trying to redeem is not available.

redeem_success.title: Levely Rewards
redeem_success.description: Awesome! You've redeemed your credits for a subscription. You can now use Levely's premium features until your subscription runs out. Have fun!

nodata.title: Huh?
nodata.description: It seems as if there isn't enough data to make this command work. Try chatting some more or get the whole server to talk and try again in a minute.

confirm.title: Import from Another Service
confirm.description: Are you sure you'd like to import data? This will **completely** override your current data with Levely. If you decided to change you mind after importing, please contact [Levely Support]({{ .support_url }}) and we will attempt to restore data.

success.title: Import from Another Service
success.description: Congrats! Levely has successfully imported data from the service you specified. Check it out with `/leaderboard`!
